Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Gochujang Butter Beans and Tenderstem® in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

In the meantime, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

== Tenderstem® and Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%mins}.

Add a splash of @water{}, then cover with a lid (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until tender, ~{4-6%mins} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once tender, add the garlic and @Tomato Puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add the cannellini beans, @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} to the broccoli pan.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, then lower to a simmer.

Cook until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Once wilted, remove from the heat.

Stir in the @Butter{20%g} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} until melted.

== To Serve ==

Share your rice between your serving #bowls{}.

Top with your gochujang cannellini beans.

Finish by sprinkling over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!